                                     <p>Solarize Frederick County is a special pilot project of the Renewable Star Challenge to encourage the adoption of home solar power by deploying a coordinated community outreach effort, combined with a tiered pricing structure. The more residents who sign up to install solar, the more the price decreases for everyone who participates in the community. And because the installer, the technology and the exact prices are provided upfront, it is much easier for residents to make the decision to go solar. Astrum Solar is the selected installer for solar electric (PV).</p>
                                      <p>FOR EVENTS AND MORE INFORMATION VISIT:<br /><a href="http://www.frederickcountymd.gov/index.aspx?NID=5350" target="_blank">http://www.frederickcountymd.gov/index.aspx?NID=5350</a></p>
                                     <p>You must register with the <a href="http://www.frederickcountymd.gov/index.aspx?NID=3531" target="_blank">Green Homes Challenge</a> to participate in the Solarize Frederick County program. A limited number of local incentive grants ($2,000 &ndash; 2,500) are available to offset the costs of a purchased solar PV system. Residents certified as <a href="http://www.frederickcountymd.gov/documents/6616/6617/6628/oes_pshb_FINAL%20Spring%202012_201206221228345763.pdf" target="_blank">Power Savers</a> in the Green Homes Challenge earn the higher grant amount. The Solarize incentive grant is in addition to the Federal tax credit and other generous state solar incentives available in Maryland. Residents opting to lease solar PV can take advantage of the program volume discounts, but are not eligible for the Solarize incentive grants.</p>  

